date=|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/priyanka-chopra-nick-jonas-donate-to-pm-cares-fund-unicef-say-no-amount-is-too-small-even-if-it-s-1-dollar/story-h7YESFtZ3vv1ANbm8jy6VL.html|title=Priyanka Chopra, Nick Jonas donate to PM-Cares fund, Unicef, say \u2018No amount is too small, even if it\u2019s 1 dollar\u2019|date=2020-03-31|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n[[Delhi Metro Rail Corporation]] donated one day salary of its 14500 employees.<ref>{{Cite news|last=ANI|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/covid-19-dmrc-donates-one-day-s-pay-of-its-employees-to-pm-cares-fund-120033001679_1.html|title=COVID-19: DMRC donates one day's pay of its employees to PM-CARES Fund|date=2020-03-30|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nEmployees of [[Software Technology Parks of India]] (STPI) under Ministry of Electronics and IT donated their one day salary through voluntary contributions to PM CARES Fund.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/business/2020/mar/30/covid-19-software-technology-parks-of-india-employees-donate-one-day-salary-to-pm-cares-fund-2123433.html|title=COVID-19: Software Technology Parks of India employees donate one-day salary to PM-CARES Fund|last=|first=|date=30 March 2020|website=The New Indian Express|others=PTI|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nPresident [[Ram Nath Kovind]] will donate a month's salary to the fund. Many other politicians including the Vice President, the [[Speaker of the Lok Sabha|Lok Sabha Speaker]] and Union Ministers made similiar commitments.<ref name=\":6\" />\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[Prime Minister's National Relief Fund]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:Government schemes in India]]\n[[Category:Modi administration initiatives]]\n[[Category:Narendra Modi]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Prime Minister's Citizen Assistance and Relief in Emergency Situations Fund''' '''(PM CARES Fund)''' was created on 28 March 2020 following the [[COVID-19 pandemic in India]]. The fund will be used for combating, containment and relief efforts against the coronavirus outbreak and similar pandemic like situations in the future. The Prime Minister is the chairman of the trust. Members will include the defence, home and finance ministers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/pm-cares-pm-narendra-modi-announces-new-covid-19-fund-gets-rs-25-crore-from-akshay-kumar-2202275|title=PM Modi Announces New COVID-19 Fund, Gets Rs 25 Crore From Akshay Kumar|last=|first=|date=|editor-last=Roy|editor-first=Divyanshu Dutta|website=NDTV|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newsonair.com/Main-News-Details.aspx?id=384047|title=People urged to donate generously in PM CARES fund; PM Modi says every contribution matters|website=newsonair.com|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/pm-narendra-modi-announces-pm-cares-fund-to-fight-coronavirus-outbreak-120032900031_1.html|title=PM Narendra Modi announces PM-CARES fund to fight coronavirus outbreak|date=2020-03-29|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-03-29|url-status=live|others=PTI}}</ref>\n\nThe fund will also enable [[micro-donation]]s.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Sharma|first=Sandhya|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/tech/internet/cyber-chiefs-warning-as-hackers-target-pms-covid-fund/articleshow/74877953.cms|title=Cyber chief's warning as hackers target PM's Covid fund|date=2020-03-29|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> The minimum donation accepted for the PM CARES Fund is {{INRConvert|10||lk=on|year=2020}}.<ref name=\":3\" /> The donations will be tax exempt and fall under [[corporate social responsibility]].<ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/economy/policy/donation-to-pm-cares-fund-to-be-fully-exempted-under-income-tax-act/article31221733.ece|title=Donation to PM CARES Fund to be fully exempted section 80G of I-T Act|last=|first=|date=31 March 2020|website=The Hindu @businessline|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> The Prime Minister had said that the [[Prime Minister's Office (India)|PMO]] had received many requests to help in the war against COVID-19. Accordingly, the fund was set up and will be used for disaster management and research.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dqindia.com/pm-cares-fund-need-know/|title=PM CARES Fund: All You Need to Know|date=2020-03-30|website=DATAQUEST|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/pm-modi-announces-emergency-relief-fund-for-coronavirus-fight/articleshow/74863297.cms|title=PM Modi announces emergency relief fund for coronavirus fight|date=2020-03-28|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, Syed Ataur Rahman, a citizen of India, donated {{INRConvert|501||lk=on|year=2020}} to the fund tweeting about it as \"just a little donation\". PM Modi tweeted back that \"There\u2019s nothing big or little. Every single contribution matters. It shows our collective resolve to defeat COVID-19.\"<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/prime-minister-narendra-modi-to-man-who-donated-rs-501-to-covid-19-coronavirus-fund-nothing-big-or-l-2202366|title=\"Nothing Big Or Little\": PM To Man Who Donated Rs 501 To COVID-19 Fund|last=|first=|date=|website=NDTV|others=PTI|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n== About ==\nAny contribution made to the PM CARES Fund before 30 June would qualify for a full amount of [[tax exemption]] under (80G) [[The Income-tax Act, 1961|Income Tax Act, 1961]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|last=Noronha|first=Gaurav|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/govt-clarifies-on-companys-contributions-to-pm-cares-fund-above-csr-limit/articleshow/74907220.cms|title=Govt clarifies on company's contributions to PM CARES Fund above CSR limit|date=2020-03-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref><ref name=\":7\" /> The [[Ministry of Corporate Affairs]] announced that contributions to the PM CARES fund would be counted as part of the companies corporate social responsibility with additional CSR being offset in subsequent years.<ref name=\":2\" />\n\nThe PM CARES fund is different from the [[Prime Minister's National Relief Fund]] (PMNRF), which was created in 1948 and has been used by the [[Government of India]] ever since, for example during the recent [[2013 North India floods]], the [[2015 South India floods]] and the [[2019 Kerala floods]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pmindia.gov.in/en/pms-funds/|title=PM National Relief Fund {{!}} Prime Minister of India|website=www.pmindia.gov.in|language=en|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the creation of the fund opposition members raised a queries as to why a separate fund was needed, when it was registered, under which act and why it did not contain any members of civil society or opposition as part of the trust.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/congress-questions-setting-up-of-pm-cares-fund-to-deal-with-coronavirus/article31210904.ece|title=Congress questions setting up of PM CARES Fund to deal with coronavirus|date=2020-03-30|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-03-31|others=Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> [[Business Today (India)|Business Today]] reported that government sources justified creation of the fund saying that PMNRF is for natural disasters, while PM CARES Fund is for COVID-19 similar pandemic situations.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstoday.in/current/economy-politics/pm-cares-fund-better-suited-tto-deal-with-coronavirus-crisis-say-legal-experts/story/399670.html|title=PM CARES Fund better suited to deal with coronavirus crisis, say legal experts|website=www.businesstoday.in|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> It was also mentioned that the [[Consolidated Fund of India]] needs legislative jurisdiction to be used; creation of a fund like the PM CARES Fund takes care of legislative hurdles.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nImmediately after the fund was created a number of fake accounts popped up. While the original [[Unified Payments Interface|UPI]] account was PMCARES@SBI, [[Delhi Police]] booked unknown individuals for creating an account removing the 'S', PMCARE@SBI, intended to scam people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/delhi-police-books-fraudsters-for-making-fake-sbi-account-of-pm-s-covid-19-relief-fund-1661272-2020-03-30|title=Delhi Police books fraudsters for making fake SBI account of PM's Covid-19 Relief Fund|last=Ojha|first=Arvind|date=30 March 2020|website=India Today|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== Contributions ==\nThe day the fund was announced, Syed Ataur Rahman, a citizen of India, donated {{INRConvert|501||lk=on|year=2020}} tweeting about it as \"just a little donation\". PM Modi tweeted back that \"There\u2019s nothing big or little. Every single contribution matters. It shows our collective resolve to defeat COVID-19.\"<ref name=\":5\" />\n\nFollowing is an incomplete list of contributions to the PM CARES Fund above {{INRConvert|25|c|lk=on|year=2020}} for companies and above {{INRConvert|10|c|lk=on|year=2020}} for individuals:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Incomplete list of contributions\n!Name of company/PSU\n!Amount (Rs)\n!Name of person\n!Amount (Rs)\n|-\n|[[Tata Group]] (Tata Sons and Tata Trusts)\n|{{INRConvert|1500|c|lk=on|year=2020}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-ZtNZKBroO/?igshid=mldr8ae8sev4|title=Tata Group commits INR 500 crores for PM-CARE